description:
On the E. edge of big tomb.
[plan]
[plan]
In a pit in the gebel a vault of bricks
The tomb was plundered through a hole in the roof. Skulls of a young woman & child. Objects in rubbish. Built of very large bricks coated, with mud.
Edward R. Ayrton.

description:
Cemetery: Beyond gabbâna
Intact
Shallow trench, 50 cm deep containing childs body in small wooden coffin. Body supine, slightly on left side, head bent up.
N.W & S.E. face to W.
At the throat were
2 small blue glaze amulets
5 carnelian spherical beads
Many very small bl. glaze beads forming a single string.
inputBy: Amanda Ford Spora; Susan Magyarody; Denis Antoine
